body:
As can be seen [here](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/3360024a0b2a55a9093ef477b097e4bbaa612cb5/onnxruntime/core/framework/allocator.cc#L58-L74), CreateMemoryInfo doesn't support DML EP today, but if you know the shape of the output a priori and can allocate memory for it using the appropriate device allocator, you don't need it (memory info). We've had one other ask to support this in DML EP, so marking this as an enhancement.
cc @fdwr
@simonbunge Coincidentally we are currently evaluating how to best expose this in the API for other customers too. No need to apologize for information requests! Stay tuned... FYI @gineshidalgo99

> As can be seen [here](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/3360024a0b2a55a9093ef477b097e4bbaa612cb5/onnxruntime/core/framework/allocator.cc#L58-L74), CreateMemoryInfo doesn't support DML EP today, but if you know the shape of the output a priori and can allocate memory for it using the appropriate device allocator, you don't need it (memory info). We've had one other ask to support this in DML EP, so marking this as an enhancement. cc @fdwr

Thanks, @pranavsharma! Assuming I can pre-determine the dimensions (tricky for my application, but probably doable): can you give me a hint how the allocation would work for the DML EP? As in: a code snippet that shows how to (without using CreateTensor() whose overloads would all seem to require a MemoryInfo) create a Value that I can feed to BindInput()/ BindOutput()?
@simonbunge FYI the pending PR is here: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/pull/9686

@simonbunge (clearing up old issues) For https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/10279, I shared a standalone sanity test app [here (main.cpp)](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/files/7917063/main.txt). *Update 2022-06-02 newer version version here https://github.com/fdwr/OnnxRuntimeDirectMLEPSample. Does that help? Our partner team will be working on a more *official* sample, and I should add it to the docs too.

issue.title: onnxruntime c++ inference using CUDA and iobinding
issue.body: Hi, I saw your question here https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/9584 with the subject: Handling Ort::IoBinding for DirectML EP (C++)? From your description, you It seems that inference using CUDA and iobinding (c++) is already implemented? Would you like to share your implementation? I don't know how to implement iobinding when using onnxruntime c++ to avoid useless transfer of data between GPU and CPU, I can't find enough information, if you can give me some guidance, I Will be very grateful, thank you.
